# Creating a profile

If this is your first time running Xeres, you need to create a **profile** and a **location**.

The profile is basically yourself (a person) and the location is your machine. You can have several locations, like a desktop and a laptop, each running your profile.

It's possible to export a profile from your first machine to use it on another. Use the `Tools / Export` menu for that, then import it in the account creation on your other machine.

# Adding Friends

While Xeres can run by itself, it's much more interesting when you start connecting to some friends.

The main concept for that is an exchange of IDs. You give your ID to your friends, and your friends gives their ID to you. Only if you do this exchange, you can be connected together.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

You can do that directly from the **Home** panel. Press the following button at the right of your ID to copy it to the clipboard.

![Copy To Clipboard](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

You can then paste that ID in the medium of your choice to send to your friend, for example:

- another chat app
- email
- SMS
- text file on a USB stick

Once your friend gave his ID to you, press the **Add Peer** button.

![Add Peer](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

This will bring the following window where you can paste your friend’s ID and press the **Add** button.

![Adding Friend](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Once this 2-way ID exchange is done, Xeres will connect directly and securely, without using any 3rd party server.

Note: there's also an online [ChatServer](https://retroshare.ch/) available, if you just want to try the software or are looking for friends.

Hint: you can also use the QR code button, take a picture with your smartphone and show it to the other instance of Xeres by using the little QR code scanner button in the add peer window.
